The paper deals with rational behavior in cryptographic protocols, which is a topic that falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses game theory concepts such as subgame perfection and Nash equilibrium, which are relevant to the category of theoretical computer science (cs.GT). Additionally, the paper discusses computational complexity and asymptotic security, which are relevant to the categories of information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper proposes a new solution concept called threat-free Nash equilibrium, which is related to the category of computational complexity (cs.CC).
